        "author": "IARPA STONESOUP Test and Evaluation team",
        "description": "This test case implements an unchecked write into a stack allocated buffer. The buffer is declared as a fixed size local variable within a function. Untrusted input is not properly sanitized or restricted before being copied into the target buffer, resulting in a buffer overflow. The overflow potentially modifies other local variables, depending on the layout of the stack. If the stack grows downward, the overflow will eventually overwrite %eip, smashing the stack or setting it to a valid instruction. \nMetadata\n - Base program: PostgreSQL\n - Source Taint: FILE_CONTENTS\n - Data Type: STRUCT\n - Data Flow: ADDRESS_AS_VARIABLE\n - Control Flow: INFINITE_LOOP",
